### ARTICLE C: NON-NEGOTIABLE RESTRICTIONS ON USE

Your right to use, modify, or distribute the Software is conditional upon your strict adherence to the following restrictions. Violation of any of these restrictions constitutes an act of bad faith and results in immediate termination of this license.

C.1. **PROHIBITED USES**: The Software shall not be used, directly or indirectly, for any of the following purposes:
    a) **State-Sponsored Disinformation**: Use by any state-level actor, intelligence agency, or state-affiliated entity for the purpose of creating, refining, or disseminating propaganda or disinformation.
    b) **Suppression of Speech**: Integration into any system designed for the automated censorship, moderation, or suppression of lawful speech.
    c) **Surveillance**: Use in any application related to mass surveillance, social scoring, or predictive policing.
    d) **Military Application**: Use in any military, intelligence, or offensive cyberwarfare operations.
    e) **Harassment**: Use to generate content intended to harass, defame, intimidate, or harm any individual or group.

C.2. **BRANDING AND ATTRIBUTION**:
    a) **No Use of Svitlogics Brand**: This license **DOES NOT** grant any right to use the name "Svitlogics," the Svitlogics logo, or any associated trademarks. Any public-facing Derivative Work **MUST** operate under a fundamentally different and non-confusing brand.
    b) **Mandatory Attribution**: Any public-facing Derivative Work **MUST** include the following notice, clearly visible to end-users (e.g., in a footer or "About" section), with a direct, clickable link to the original repository:
       > "This software is based on the open-source Svitlogics project, developed by Eugene Kozlovsky in Kyiv, Ukraine. The original project is available at https://github.com/koztechie/svitlogics and is licensed under the Svitlogics Software License Agreement."

C.3. **DATA PRIVACY OBLIGATIONS FOR DERIVATIVE WORKS**:
    a) **Stateless by Default**: You acknowledge that the canonical Software is stateless.
    b) **Strict Liability for Data Storage**: If you modify the Software to store any user-submitted text or personally identifiable information, you assume **strict and total liability** for the security of that data and for compliance with all applicable data protection laws (e.g., GDPR, CCPA). You agree to indemnify and hold harmless the Author from any and all claims, damages, or legal actions arising from your decision to store user data.

